<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-11-15T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-11-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.6831/209: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-11-15T18:00:00+02:00">November 15, 1938—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November 15—2:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>64. <hi rend="italic">Modus vivendi</hi> signed. As it seemed
                                preferable not to include exceptions in the body of the agreement, I
                                have proposed and request the Department’s permission to address a
                                note to the Minister for Foreign Affairs incorporating the language
                                suggested in the Department’s instruction 492, October 12 except for
                                the omission of “sardines in brine”, which the Greeks are willing to
                                drop.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>